  "description": [
    "NATIONAL INTELLIGENCER MANIFEST DESTINY Our readers we are sure will have noticed a fact to which allusion has heretofore been made in this journal concerning the marked decline of that filibustering spirit which has more than once been unhappily prevalent in certain sections of the coun try We are not insensible of the various causes which have contributed to this result among which we find a pleasure in mentioning the firmness with which the Executive Head of the Government de nounced by his official proclamation these disorgan izing schemes as being no less a violation of our own laws than an infringement of those which bind together the commonwealth of nations in a commu nity of rights and correlative duties It is no less grateful to us to recall the disapprobation with which the popular branch of Congress received the illadvised proposition to repeal with respect to a European Power with whom we are still in relations of ostensible peace and amity those Neutrality Laws with which the legislation of Congress has sanctioned and ratified the Common Law of Na tions And we may allude to the fidelity and rigor with which the Judiciary has applied the princi pies of"
